<div style="margin-bottom: 10px">
  <h3>
    <a href="/p/whonix/featureblog/2013/03/whonix-64-bit-custom-builds-freebsd-kernel-based-builds/">Whonix 64 bit custom builds; #FreeBSD Kernel based builds</a>
  </h3>
  <div class="markdown_content"><p>Since Whonix 0.6.1 (Developer Preview version), it's trivial to create 64 bit builds of Whonix. If you already know how to build Whonix from source code, only a very few steps are missing.</p>
<p>Simply get into Whonix build-steps folder and open the 20_create-debian-img step.</p>
<p>On Github:<br />
<a href="https://github.com/adrelanos/Whonix/blob/development/build-steps/20_create-debian-img" rel="nofollow">https://github.com/adrelanos/Whonix/blob/development/build-steps/20_create-debian-img</a></p>
<p>For example, you can comment out.</p>
<div class="codehilite"><pre><span class="c">#local ARCH=&quot;i386&quot;... [read more](/p/whonix/featureblog/2013/03/whonix-64-bit-custom-builds-freebsd-kernel-based-builds/)</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
  <em class="grid-19">
    Posted by <a href="/u/adrelanos/">
    
  
    <img src="https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/e6d471603b9691707b0445c54f04d460?r=pg"
